== Compile ==

    make clean
    make server
    make client4

== Run Server ==

    ./server <port>

    For example:

    ./server 8207

    The server accepts connections from both its IPv4 and IPv6 addresses.

== Run IPv4 Client ==

    ./client4 <server_ip> <server_port>

    For examples:

    ./client4 127.0.0.1 8207
    
    If the server IPv4 address is 192.168.0.1, then run:

    ./client4 192.168.0.1 8207

